    "body": "@takluyver yes, it can, sometimes. It just needs to remeasure all the elements around it, because it's the container that's resized on transition, and the cell fills the available size. If we add media queries to the cell, we would need to make sure it measures the padding and margins of prompts, etc. at every level correctly. Plus, for continuously varied widths (screen < 768px, I believe), it would still need to measure and reset max-width on every window resize.\n"
